1
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:10,967
<i>I'm affected
because my parents fought again.</i>

2
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:13,167
<i>You're not alone, Jas. I'm here.</i>

3
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,233
<i> You know, sometimes...</i>

4
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:16,033
<i>I wish you were more like my mom
used to be.</i>

5
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:18,567
<i>She was always with dad
at business meetings.</i>

6
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:19,967
<i> She was always there.</i>

7
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:22,667
<i>They didn't have a kid
like Jasmine.</i>

8
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,733
<i>She didn't have a mom
with issues</i>

9
00:00:24,867 --> 00:00:26,433
<i>or a brother
she had to look after.</i>

10
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:28,767
<i> Their life isn't our life.</i>

11
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:30,333
<i>Didn't I tell you
not to go out?</i>

12
00:00:30,467 --> 00:00:32,667
<i>Even if grandmother said yes,
it's still not allowed?</i>

13
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,133
<i> Let me remind you, Marj.</i>

14
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:35,600
<i> Jasmine is my granddaughter.</i>

15
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,233
<i> And I love her, too.</i>

16
00:00:37,367 --> 00:00:39,833
<i>So you can't stop me
from stepping in</i>

17
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:42,567
<i>every time she feels suffocated
by you.</i>

18
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,200
<i>Where's the Marj
I fell in love with?</i>

19
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:46,600
<i>Not the mom whose whole world
revolves around Jasmine.</i>

20
00:00:46,733 --> 00:00:48,767
<i>When did you ever choose
to stand beside me?</i>

21
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:51,267
<i>When did you ever try
to understand me?</i>

22
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:54,667
Me too, Marj.

23
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:58,367
Do you think
this is easy for me?

24
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:03,267
I fight for this family
in ways you don't see.

25
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,867
With people. At work.

26
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:09,133
With problems I don't
even bring home to you.

27
00:01:10,533 --> 00:01:11,667
But, Marj...

28
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:16,900
if you're pushing me away, too,

29
00:01:17,933 --> 00:01:20,667
like you're the only one who
knows what's best for Jasmine

30
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,133
because you claim her
like she's yours alone...

31
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:28,233
where does that leave me?

32
00:02:42,967 --> 00:02:45,933
<i> Surprise! Happy birthday!</i>

33
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,300
Why are you still awake?

34
00:02:49,767 --> 00:02:51,467
It's your birthday.

35
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:53,000
I'm required to be first.

36
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,800
Make a wish,
even if it's virtual.

37
00:03:14,667 --> 00:03:17,233
<i> Mom might catch me.</i>

38
00:03:17,367 --> 00:03:19,167
She told me to sleep already.

39
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:23,300
I really wish you could come.

40
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:24,700
Why?

41
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,900
Is that your virtual wish?

42
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:31,567
Okay.

43
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:33,467
Good night.

44
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:35,500
Breathe. Ready?

45
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,000
Ready when you are.

46
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:41,600
- One, two...
- One, two...

47
00:03:43,167 --> 00:03:44,500
- three.
- three.

48
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:54,467
- We got this.
- We got this.

49
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:06,233
Jasmine's birthday party
is so grand.

50
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:09,900
She's only 16, but it's
practically like a debut.

51
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:11,833
Well, she's Sir Greg's
first granddaughter.

52
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:14,300
Of course,
it has to be fancy.

53
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:15,400
Yeah, it's fancy,

54
00:04:15,533 --> 00:04:19,300
but Ma'am Marj and Sir Paolo
are always fighting.

55
00:04:20,167 --> 00:04:21,533
<i> All that effort is wasted.</i>

56
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:23,833
If I were Jasmine,
I'd be so upset.

57
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:27,733
- I swear.
- Hey, keep your voice down.

58
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:31,500
It's not easy for Ma'am Marj,
you know that.

59
00:04:31,633 --> 00:04:33,267
That's true, Yolly.

60
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:36,700
But you can feel it.
It's intense here every day.

61
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:37,967
Yeah.

62
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:41,600
Totally different
from Sir Edward's family vibes.

63
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:43,067
It's like...

64
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,400
they're so smooth. So chill.

65
00:04:45,533 --> 00:04:48,100
<i>How would you know?
They're in Cebu.</i>

66
00:04:49,967 --> 00:04:52,467
I follow Ma'am Thea
on social media.

67
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:56,333
Oh my gosh, Yolly,
it's all shopping!

68
00:04:56,467 --> 00:04:59,500
Out of the country,
as in abroad.

69
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:02,700
And speaking of shopping,
everything's branded.

70
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:05,133
<i> They look so happy in Cebu.</i>

71
00:05:05,267 --> 00:05:07,833
Must be nice, right?

72
00:05:07,967 --> 00:05:10,833
Just because people look happy
in photos and videos

73
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:13,433
doesn't mean they really are.

74
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:17,233
Sometimes a smile...

75
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:18,733
is just for the camera.

76
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,133
I just hope
Jasmine's happy tonight.

77
00:05:24,267 --> 00:05:28,667
And I hope the adults
call a ceasefire.

78
00:05:31,633 --> 00:05:32,667
I hope so.

79
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,333
Are you ready
for your party tonight?

80
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:53,900
Jas.

81
00:05:56,967 --> 00:05:59,200
I'm sorry about what happened
last time.

82
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:03,000
I know things haven't been easy
lately,

83
00:06:03,133 --> 00:06:05,267
and maybe I've been too much.

84
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:09,000
But, Sweetheart,
I just want you safe.

85
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:10,933
I know.

86
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:14,433
I never meant to make you worry.

87
00:06:14,567 --> 00:06:17,233
Or make you and dad,
or you and grandmother, fight.

88
00:06:17,367 --> 00:06:19,267
It just feels like
there's always a fight

89
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,233
whenever I want something.

90
00:06:22,667 --> 00:06:23,700
Baby, you are not the reason

91
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:29,100
your dad and I, or your
grandmother and I, argue.

92
00:06:29,233 --> 00:06:30,600
It's not you.

93
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:32,867
Never you.

94
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:35,500
But, Mom, no matter what I do,

95
00:06:37,567 --> 00:06:40,300
I'm always being watched.

96
00:06:40,633 --> 00:06:42,433
There's always something
I'm not allowed to do.

97
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,667
There's always caution.

98
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,267
I'm trying.

99
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,833
But I hope someday...

100
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,233
you can feel
that I can handle things,

101
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:56,133
even just a little.

102
00:06:57,267 --> 00:06:59,900
Jasmine, I want to believe that.

103
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:05,533
I'm just so used to watching
your every breath.

104
00:07:05,667 --> 00:07:08,300
I can't just switch
that off overnight.

105
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:12,600
I'll tell you where I'm going.

106
00:07:12,733 --> 00:07:14,133
I'll be careful.

107
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:18,633
But please...

108
00:07:18,767 --> 00:07:20,533
let me try sometimes.

109
00:07:20,667 --> 00:07:22,900
So I don't feel
like I'm trapped.

110
00:07:24,367 --> 00:07:25,400
Okay, Sweetheart.

111
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,033
I'll try.

112
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:30,567
I'll try.

113
00:07:31,733 --> 00:07:35,300
I don't want to be the reason
you're unhappy.

114
00:07:35,433 --> 00:07:39,000
I won't stop you from doing
what you want to do anymore.

115
00:07:40,867 --> 00:07:42,800
I'll do my best.

116
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:47,467
Just promise me you'll
take care of yourself.

117
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,967
I will, Mom.

118
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,433
Just please don't freak out
right away.

119
00:07:54,567 --> 00:07:55,967
I love you.

120
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:03,967
I love you so much.

121
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:09,767
My baby's really
a young lady now.

122
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:18,367
<i>- Happy birthday, Jasmine.
- Hello, thank you, thank you.</i>

123
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,867
Enjoy.

124
00:08:24,267 --> 00:08:25,933
Happy birthday,
my granddaughter.

125
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:28,600
Thank you, Grandfather.
I'm really happy you're here.

126
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:31,633
You look stunning, Darling.

127
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:33,533
Happy birthday.

128
00:08:33,667 --> 00:08:35,333
Enjoy your night.

129
00:08:35,467 --> 00:08:38,567
Don't let anyone
ruin your happiness.

130
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:40,500
Thank you, Grandmother.

131
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:45,333
Jasmine, happy birthday.

132
00:08:45,467 --> 00:08:46,867
Thanks, Dad.

133
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,000
- Mom.
- Marj.

134
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:01,233
Jobert.

135
00:09:02,267 --> 00:09:03,100
Hello.

136
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:04,200
Mom.

137
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,900
Marj.

138
00:09:06,033 --> 00:09:07,267
Marj!

139
00:09:09,033 --> 00:09:11,833
Wow, look at my brother.

140
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:14,567
Wow, Marj.
The setup is so beautiful.

141
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:17,067
Jasmine's only 16, and this
already feels like a debut.

142
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:21,667
Marj, happy birthday
to Baby Jasmine.

143
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:25,567
I want to see her.

144
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,633
I'm a good boy today.

145
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,233
Good boy.

146
00:09:30,367 --> 00:09:33,600
Don't make me leave like before.

147
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:34,500
No.

148
00:09:34,633 --> 00:09:37,233
Jobert, nobody's making you
leave.

149
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:39,633
Jasmine invited you herself.

150
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:42,367
You know, there's spaghetti.
Lots of food.

151
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:45,333
Your favorite,
spaghetti and chicken.

152
00:09:45,467 --> 00:09:48,300
I'll take care of you, okay?

153
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:49,633
Go on, look over there.

154
00:09:49,767 --> 00:09:51,233
- We'll go ahead.
- Okay.

155
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,133
Spaghetti.

156
00:09:55,267 --> 00:09:56,933
Marj...

157
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:59,033
are you and Paolo okay now?

158
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,933
Mom, let's talk later.

159
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:05,867
The party's about to start.

160
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,633
<i>- Jas!
- Jas!</i>

161
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:22,500
Jas! Happy birthday!

162
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:25,333
Girl, you're
blooming this summer.

163
00:10:25,467 --> 00:10:27,700
Pretty sure we already know
who's prom queen

164
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,567
when school starts.

165
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:32,867
Hey, Jas.

166
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:36,167
- Happy birthday.
- Hi, Xander.

167
00:10:36,467 --> 00:10:37,467
Thanks.

168
00:10:37,733 --> 00:10:40,333
I thought you were out of town.

169
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:41,633
I came back early.

170
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:43,067
Didn't want to miss this.

171
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:48,833
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

172
00:10:48,967 --> 00:10:54,367
Let's all welcome our birthday
girl, Jasmine Torrecampo!

173
00:10:57,067 --> 00:10:59,333
- Wait.
- Yeah, yeah. Go.

174
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:00,467
We'll be here.

175
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:04,267
- I'm not going anywhere.
- See you.

176
00:11:28,133 --> 00:11:29,500
Well...

177
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:31,433
sixteen candles.

178
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:35,667
You know, when I was little,

179
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:39,267
even blowing out one candle
was hard for me.

180
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:45,567
I even had this thing,
an incentive spirometer.

181
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:46,967
They'd make me use it

182
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:51,200
so I'd learn to breathe
without getting tired.

183
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:52,933
And now...

184
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:54,800
sixteen candles.

185
00:11:56,533 --> 00:12:01,900
And I can proudly say
I can blow them out on my own.

186
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:06,300
Sixteen candles.

187
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:08,700
Sixteen wishes.

188
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:11,133
But honestly...

189
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:13,500
I really just have one.

190
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,300
I just want more days

191
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:19,133
where it feels good to breathe
at home.

192
00:12:19,267 --> 00:12:21,067
<i> In life.</i>

193
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,833
<i> Days that don't feel heavy,</i>

194
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:26,533
that don't feel suffocating.

195
00:12:26,667 --> 00:12:31,467
Days with space for me,
and for my family.

196
00:12:33,267 --> 00:12:35,067
<i> Mom. Dad.</i>

197
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:39,700
You were the first ones
who taught me how to breathe.

198
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,100
How to love.

199
00:12:42,233 --> 00:12:45,667
How to live
with someone beside you.

200
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:50,933
So I hope you don't forget how
to do that for each other, too.

201
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,733
<i> I'm rooting for us.</i>

202
00:12:52,867 --> 00:12:56,000
Even when the world
feels tight...

203
00:12:57,133 --> 00:12:59,300
you're still my home.

204
00:13:28,867 --> 00:13:31,900
What Jasmine said earlier...

205
00:13:32,967 --> 00:13:35,467
I didn't realize...

206
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,300
it was that heavy for her.

207
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:41,367
She's been affected, too.

208
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:45,700
I neglected us.

209
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:48,067
Hon, I burned out. And you...

210
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:53,167
Love...

211
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,000
it's not just you
who fell short.

212
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,467
Maybe...

213
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:01,967
I should've given you
a little breather.

214
00:14:04,667 --> 00:14:06,433
I can support you...

215
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:11,867
so we can find time
for each other again.

216
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:21,300
Let's go to Jasmine.

217
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,867
<i>We'll put our gifts
on the table.</i>

218
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,900
We'll go see Sofia, too.

219
00:14:30,067 --> 00:14:31,167
See you, guys.

220
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,800
I'll just put this
on the gift table.

221
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:37,067
Hello.

222
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Hello.

223
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,100
Hi, Sweetheart.

224
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:46,000
We heard everything
you said earlier.

225
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:49,733
And we promise to do our best.

226
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:53,400
Jasmine...

227
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:54,800
We'll do better.

228
00:14:54,933 --> 00:14:57,133
We'll fix things together.

229
00:14:57,267 --> 00:14:58,733
As a family.

230
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,700
Happy birthday, Baby.

231
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,367
Jasmine!

232
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:13,967
Ash!

233
00:15:20,267 --> 00:15:22,067
I missed you so much!

234
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:26,500
- Hi, Uncle. Hi, Auntie.
- Hi!

235
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:31,033
I can't believe you made it.

236
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:33,533
You surprised me.
I thought you weren't coming.

237
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:35,500
Mom and dad agreed
to come with me.

238
00:15:35,667 --> 00:15:37,100
They missed you, too.

239
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,300
Ash, where are
uncle and auntie?

240
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,800
Hi, Marj!

241
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:13,700
- Jasmine, happy birthday.
- Hi, Auntie.

242
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:16,967
- Thank you. Hi, Uncle.
- Happy birthday, Jasmine.

243
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:19,933
Perfect timing for a reunion,
right?

244
00:16:20,067 --> 00:16:22,100
So, did you miss us?

245
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:34,467
Good thing you made it.

246
00:16:34,867 --> 00:16:35,867
Of course.

247
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,133
I wouldn't miss this
for the world.

248
00:16:38,267 --> 00:16:41,867
We came straight here
from the airport.

249
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:44,533
- Here's your gift.
- Thanks, Uncle Edward.

250
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:47,167
I picked that out myself.
But open it later.

251
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:48,667
Over there.

252
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:51,567
<i> Oh my goodness!</i>

253
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:53,800
- Mommy!
- Grandmother!

254
00:16:53,933 --> 00:16:55,400
I missed you!

255
00:16:55,533 --> 00:16:57,133
- Son!
- Mom.

256
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:00,800
Edward.

257
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,233
You're here.

258
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:07,133
Dad.

259
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:11,867
- Hi, Dad.
- Hello.

260
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Hello, Grandfather.

261
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:15,567
- How are you? I missed you.
- I'm good, Sweetie.

262
00:17:15,733 --> 00:17:16,900
I missed you.

263
00:17:17,167 --> 00:17:18,067
Please bless me.

264
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:25,133
- Okay, family picture, please.
- Oh, sure.

265
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:26,500
Let's go.

266
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:28,800
<i> Hold it right there.</i>

267
00:17:32,433 --> 00:17:34,767
<i>- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you.</i>

268
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:38,733
Marj, I missed you!
You look amazing! So annoying!

269
00:17:38,867 --> 00:17:39,967
You haven't changed at all.

270
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:42,500
- It's nice to see you again.
- It's nothing.

271
00:17:42,633 --> 00:17:44,633
Oh my God,
Ashley looks like you!

272
00:17:44,767 --> 00:17:47,067
Of course. We really prepared.

273
00:17:49,133 --> 00:17:50,600
These girls are so pretty.

274
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,567
<i> They grew up so fast.</i>

275
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:55,900
I know that smell.

276
00:17:57,133 --> 00:18:00,267
That's the perfume you
were wearing that night.

277
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,300
<i>You look like your mom.
Sorry, Edward.</i>

278
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:05,700
<i>- Guess it runs in the family.
- Marj.</i>

279
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:07,967
<i> I'll just go check on dad.</i>

280
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:10,333
<i> Sure. See you later.</i>

281
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,600
It's nice to see you, dear.

282
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:19,133
I hope you guys stay longer
this time.

283
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:21,533
You're aging backwards.

284
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:22,900
Where are we going?

285
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:25,033
Come on, it'll be fun, Ash.
Hurry.

286
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:28,000
I'm really excited to show you.
Come on.

287
00:18:28,133 --> 00:18:29,367
What is this?

288
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:41,833
Oh my God, Ash.

289
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:43,567
I missed you so much.

290
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:45,433
Wasn't Christmas
the last time?

291
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:48,800
You're so dramatic.
We video call almost every day.

292
00:18:49,033 --> 00:18:50,667
It's not the same.

293
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,600
It's different when
you're actually here.

294
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:54,467
So, I prepared something.

295
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:57,033
What's that? What's inside?

296
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,600
Jasmine.

297
00:19:02,867 --> 00:19:03,667
That's not allowed.

298
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:04,800
You're not supposed to have
that, right?

299
00:19:04,933 --> 00:19:06,667
What if Aunt Marj catches us?
What are you thinking?

300
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,667
Come on, Ashley. It's just beer.
Don't be so dramatic.

301
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,967
And hello, it's my birthday.

302
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:13,067
And my best friend is here.

303
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:16,000
Nothing's stopping me
from having a little fun.

304
00:19:18,267 --> 00:19:19,633
You know what? Fine.

305
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,133
I promise,
it's going to be good.

306
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:25,167
But you behave.

307
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:28,367
I'm responsible for you,
so act right.

308
00:19:28,533 --> 00:19:30,900
Then drink responsibly with me.

309
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:33,733
- Cheers?
- Sweet sixteen.

310
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,200
What was that?

311
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,300
Never again.

312
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:16,333
Why are you alone over here?

313
00:20:17,933 --> 00:20:21,600
Every time there's an event
in Manila, you're like this.

314
00:20:23,367 --> 00:20:24,900
You know me.

315
00:20:25,033 --> 00:20:27,700
My social battery drops
when I'm here.

316
00:20:29,167 --> 00:20:30,900
This kind of thing?

317
00:20:31,033 --> 00:20:32,400
This is more Paolo's scene.

318
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:34,767
And I'm just staying
off dad's radar.

319
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:37,767
I thought you two were okay now?

320
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:40,100
Isn't he supporting
your business?

321
00:20:40,233 --> 00:20:42,500
I'm sure he's very proud of you.

322
00:20:42,633 --> 00:20:45,600
I heard Thea earlier
telling guests

323
00:20:45,733 --> 00:20:47,067
your business is thriving.

324
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:50,933
Edward, I'm really happy
for you.

325
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:55,567
You got everything
you ever wanted. Your dreams.

326
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:58,133
A successful career.

327
00:20:58,267 --> 00:21:00,033
A happy and healthy family.

328
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,700
You have it all.

329
00:21:09,767 --> 00:21:11,100
Sorry. My alarm went off.

330
00:21:11,233 --> 00:21:13,600
I need to give Jasmine
her medicines.

331
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,767
Join us later, okay?

332
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:23,333
You're wrong, Marj.

333
00:21:25,533 --> 00:21:26,867
I don't have it all.

334
00:21:37,833 --> 00:21:40,100
I'll make sure to dispose
of this, okay?

335
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:42,133
Just make sure, okay?

336
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:47,467
Oh, it's mom.
I'll see you later at the party.

337
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:49,433
- It's time for my medcines.
- Okay, okay.

338
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:50,833
See you later.

339
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,433
Sorry, Uncle.

340
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:10,433
Sorry.

341
00:22:16,367 --> 00:22:17,733
Are you okay?

342
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:18,967
I'm sorry.

343
00:22:20,633 --> 00:22:21,467
<i> Go ahead.</i>

344
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:25,467
<i> Carry your child.</i>

345
00:22:39,133 --> 00:22:40,300
<i> Choose.</i>

346
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:41,867
<i> Your conscience...</i>

347
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:44,867
<i>or losing Marj
and your daughter.</i>

348
00:22:47,733 --> 00:22:50,133
Why are you looking at me
like that?

349
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:54,867
Why are you looking at me
like that?

350
00:22:58,300 --> 00:22:59,167
Nothing, my child.

351
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,867
Oh, sorry. I mean, Ashley.

352
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:04,200
Be careful, okay?

353
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:06,800
Your dad might be looking
for you.

354
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:07,967
Okay.

355
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:21,933
Wow, Yolly!

356
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:24,500
Sir Edward's glow-up
is on another level.

357
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:26,300
He looks like a movie star.

358
00:23:26,433 --> 00:23:27,667
Oh, boy!

359
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,833
True. And Ma'am Thea, too.

360
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:31,633
She's gotten so much
prettier, right?

361
00:23:32,767 --> 00:23:34,433
<i> Yes.</i>

362
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:42,667
Yolly, aren't you happy
Sir Edward's here?

363
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:46,067
Of course, I'm happy.

364
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,500
But I don't know.

365
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:50,600
I've been noticing something.

366
00:23:51,633 --> 00:23:53,733
There's this...

367
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,533
tension in the air.
I can't explain it.

368
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,400
There she goes again.

369
00:24:01,833 --> 00:24:06,400
Like she's the only one
who senses omens and signs.

370
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:11,133
Hey, it's true though.

371
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:14,900
Sometimes I feel that heaviness,
too.

372
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,100
I don't know
about this family.

373
00:24:17,233 --> 00:24:19,700
It's like they're hiding
a lot of secrets.

374
00:24:19,933 --> 00:24:22,300
I can't point
to the details exactly.

375
00:24:22,433 --> 00:24:24,033
But you can tell
something's leaking.

376
00:24:24,167 --> 00:24:27,533
And you don't have to be
a fortune teller to sense that.

377
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,733
Oh, maybe it's nothing.

378
00:24:30,633 --> 00:24:32,300
You two are the worst.

379
00:24:32,433 --> 00:24:34,633
Your gossip energy
is rubbing off on me.

380
00:24:34,767 --> 00:24:36,367
Now I'm saying
all sorts of things.

381
00:24:37,433 --> 00:24:38,767
Hey, Weng. Hurry up over there.

382
00:24:38,900 --> 00:24:40,433
Bring the glasses out.

383
00:24:40,567 --> 00:24:42,100
- It's ready.
- You. Help Weng.

384
00:24:42,233 --> 00:24:43,667
Bring the bottles outside.

385
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:44,400
Yeah.

386
00:24:44,533 --> 00:24:45,267
Come on, hurry. I'm going!

387
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,500
Faster!

388
00:24:57,067 --> 00:24:58,100
Thank you.

389
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:18,867
Mind if I take this one?

390
00:25:22,667 --> 00:25:23,933
Thea, can you not?

391
00:25:24,067 --> 00:25:25,467
Just step away from me.

392
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,533
Don't you miss me, Paolo?

393
00:25:32,833 --> 00:25:34,633
Come on.

394
00:25:34,767 --> 00:25:37,167
It's been 16 years, Pao.

395
00:25:37,333 --> 00:25:40,333
We've been in-laws
for sixteen years.

396
00:25:40,467 --> 00:25:43,367
It's perfectly normal
for us to talk.

397
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:45,800
You don't have to avoid me.

398
00:25:45,933 --> 00:25:47,333
Or Ashley.

399
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:51,367
Thea, it's always like this.

400
00:25:51,733 --> 00:25:52,967
Every Christmas.

401
00:25:53,100 --> 00:25:55,200
Every family gathering.

402
00:25:55,333 --> 00:25:57,133
We barely even see each other.

403
00:25:58,867 --> 00:26:01,300
Don't you ever get tired
of playing this game?

404
00:26:03,300 --> 00:26:05,300
Come on, Paolo.

405
00:26:05,433 --> 00:26:07,533
I'm sure you miss your daughter,
too.

406
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:08,933
Thea, don't.

407
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,833
For the last time, stop it!

408
00:26:25,267 --> 00:26:26,433
What's going on?

409
00:26:31,333 --> 00:26:32,467
Are you two arguing?

410
00:26:40,467 --> 00:26:43,600
I'm thinking of talking
to Thea and Edward.

411
00:26:43,767 --> 00:26:46,100
If they're going back to Cebu
after this weekend,

412
00:26:46,233 --> 00:26:49,267
maybe Ashley could stay here
for a while.

413
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,933
Do you have an issue with them?

414
00:26:51,067 --> 00:26:51,833
Or with the child?

415
00:26:51,967 --> 00:26:53,967
You know what
I'm really afraid of?

416
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:56,133
One more mistake
from Sir Edward

417
00:26:56,267 --> 00:26:57,967
and it's war again
between him and his father.

418
00:26:58,100 --> 00:27:00,533
I don't want to hear him say
he was right about me...

419
00:27:00,667 --> 00:27:01,800
that I'm worthless.

420
00:27:01,933 --> 00:27:03,300
Have you told Thea?

421
00:27:03,433 --> 00:27:04,400
Not yet, Mom.

422
00:27:04,533 --> 00:27:07,067
Did you know Ashley's
on top of her class in Math?

423
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,467
She even won
the Science Fair last month.

424
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:13,133
Her last quarter report card?

425
00:27:13,267 --> 00:27:14,833
Straight A's.

426
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:17,467
Of course.
She takes after her dad.
